10... h6 11. Nd2 Be7 12. Qc2 O-O 13. O-O-O
{ Again, Black has the bishop pair, but this time we've kept a strong bishop on d3 @@StartBracket@@remember what I said about the strength of White having Bd3 in a standard Caro-Kann?@@EndBracket@@.   We again have the hook of ...h6 to target, and I fancy White's attacking prospects with f4, g4, g5 again! }
