13... Ne4 14. Rc1
{ 14.Nxe4?!  So in fairness to this move, I did say always trade in the 'One Knight' Variation of the Caro-Kann Reversed! However, whenever there is a change in pawn structure, we should be more careful with the decision to trade.  14...dxe4  15.Nd4  Bd7=  This is still completely fine, but ideally, we'd prefer to keep Black's pawn on d5 as a target @@StartBracket@@either for us to use to break the position with c4, or to attack in an endgame with our rooks on the d-file@@EndBracket@@. }
14... Kb8 15. Nd4 Bc8 16. c4
