{ We recapture the pawn and hit the weak f7-pawn. Black should defend carefully... }
19... Bg6 20. Ne5
{ Black should aim to play actively here, rather than grovel with ...Rf8. }
20... Rd2
{ 20...Rf8  21.Rfd1⩲  Black's pieces are all tied up, whereas we have all the activity and play.   A very pleasant position where Black will likely collapse in the coming moves! }
21. b4
{ A very neat move to save the b-pawn, while the a-pawn is protected by our bishop. We are taking the f7-pawn next, and this position is very close to collapse. Engine just about holds, but with some very unnatural defensive moves.   We should be very happy to reach this position! }
