5... Qb6
{ I consider this 'old mainline' to be over-ambitious for Black, since Black's structure often becomes overextended, thus allowing it to be easily attacked. Let's take a look: }
6. Qb3
{ We come to our first RULE of the London System: always meet ...Qb6 with Qb3! The reason being is that we neutralise the Black queen's activity, and we also never mind the queen trade. }
6... c4 7. Qc2 g6
{ This is Black's main move, but it's just really bad! Black aims to get in ...Bf5 @@StartBracket@@which would be really great for Black@@EndBracket@@, but it's simply too slow! We don't allow the bishop to develop to f5... }
8. e4
{ We prevent Black's optimal development, and immediately undermine Black's advanced pawns in the centre. }
8... dxe4 9. Nxc4 Qd8 10. Ne3
{ The e4-pawn is weak, and White has a great position with no weaknesses! } *

[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
