{ This is the correct path for Black. Let's see how to deal with this! } 8.
Qa4+ Bd7 9. Qc2
{ Our queen has improved @@StartBracket@@covering the f5-square@@EndBracket@@, while Black's bishop has weakened and become more passive. }
9... e6 10. e3 Rc8 11. Bd3 Be7 12. O-O
{ White has the better bishops. Our light-squared bishop eyes up Black's kingside, while our dark-squared bishop covers the b8- and c7-squares.   As a plan, I would make improving moves @@StartBracket@@like h3, and Qe2@@EndBracket@@. Then I'd play on the queenside and c-file with Rfc1, Rc2, Rac1. }
