4... cxd4
{ Aside from leaving the b2-pawn weak with 4. Nd2, we've also left the d4-pawn hanging! However, we have a great tactical combination up our sleeve! }
5. Nc4
{ Due to this surprising move, White will not stay a pawn down! Here, the queen has multiple squares to run to, but we will meet all the responses in the same way with: }
5... Qc5 6. cxd4
{ Another surprising blow! But this is the point: The knight is untouchable! }
6... Qxc4
{ 6...Qd5  If our opponent avoids the poisoned piece, we can simply improve our pawn structure with  7.e3  +/- and we have the much more healthy and active piece development! }
7. Rc1 { We skewer the black queen to the loose bishop on c8. } *

