{ We start with our London System move order since the bishop is actually great on f4! Importantly, we discourage the ...e5 push — which is one of Black's main ideas in the Dutch.   Here, Black has a choice of multiple Dutch systems. The Killer Dutch which I referenced earlier starts with 3...e6 — also known as the Classical Dutch. Then there's also the Leningrad Dutch with 3...g6. And finally, the Stonewall Dutch with 3...d5. Each of these Dutches has a unique flavour to them, so we'll analyse each system in turn! }
3... d5
