[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "📖 Model games: London System"]
[Black "Model Game: 1...d5 London (A Common Blunder from our Opponent!)"]
[Result "*"]

{ One of my teammates experimented with 1. c3 in the 4NCL Online @@StartBracket@@the main online league in the UK for relatively serious 45+15 online chess@@EndBracket@@!   Let's see how it went for them! }
1. c3 Nf6 2. d4 d5 3. Bf4 c6 4. e3
{ At this moment, we should already start thinking about our three ideas: Nd2, Nf3, and h3. }
4... Nh5
{ Black has surprised us with hunting down our bishop before we can play h3!   What should White play? }
5. Qxh5
{ Surprise! We must always stay tactically sharp when playing chess, rather than thinking purely strategically all the time @@StartBracket@@definitely not calling myself out right now... 😅@@EndBracket@@! Black just resigned here after 30 seconds of play.   This is why we delay our knight's development to f3 — just in case our opponent is caught napping! Also, it is likely that Black had some 'London prep' against lines with 2. Nf3 / 3. Bf4. It's a very bad idea to play solely on prep, without looking at the nuanced differences of the actual position over the board! }
