[Result "*"]

{ Derbyshire Congress Open, 90+0, Michael Green @@StartBracket@@2017@@EndBracket@@ vs Dylan Wastney @@StartBracket@@1914@@EndBracket@@ }
1. c3 d5 2. Na3 e5 3. Nc2 Nf6 4. f3
{ Here, for maximum psychological impact, I stood up from the board, and started walking around the playing hall. My opponent had his head in his hands from move 4, trying to work out how to punish my opening play. }
4... Nh5 { Black is trying too hard. This is simply a waste of tempo. } 5. g3
Be7 6. Nh3 O-O 7. Nf2 f5 8. d3 b6 9. Bg2
{ Since Black has good control over e4, I want more support for the e4 push before executing it. }
9... Bb7 10. e4 f4
{ 10...fxe4  11.fxe4  dxe4  12.Qxh5+-   10...dxe4  11.fxe4∞ } 11. g4 Nf6 12.
exd5 Nxd5 13. Qe2 Bc5 14. h4 Ba6 15. Ne4 Be7 16. g5 Nd7 17. Bd2 Nc5 18. Nxc5
Bxc5 19. O-O-O Bd6
{ I have completed my development, so it is now the time to take over. } 20.
Qe4 Ne7 21. d4 exd4 22. Nxd4 Bc4 23. Bh3
{ Bringing all the pieces into the game! } 23... Bf7 24. Be6
{ 24.Ne6!  Bxe6  25.Bxe6+  Kh8  26.h5  This was even more winning.  26...Qe8   26...Ng8  27.h6  g6   27...gxh6  28.gxh6  27.h6  g6  28.Qd4+ }
24... Qe8 25. h5 Bxe6 26. Nxe6 Rf7 27. g6
{ I take my first chance to rip open Black's kingside! } 27... Rf6 28. gxh7+
Kh8 29. h6 { Adding more pressure on Black's helpless position. } 29... Nf5 30.
Qxf5 { A queen sack threatening a pawn mate — what more can we ask for? } 30...
Qxe6
{ Of course, I had to consider Qxe6 carefully before playing 30. Qxf5. But to my delight, all the lines work out in my favour!   30...Rxf5??  31.hxg7 }
31. hxg7+ Kxg7 32. Rdg1+ Kh8 33. Qg5
{ The key move I had to spot in my calculation on move 30.   Now it is game over. }
33... Qf7 34. Qg8+ { ...The point! } 34... Rxg8 35. hxg8=Q#
{ A beautiful Slug game, ending with a double check to seal the deal! I did feel a bit bad for my young opponent, but only for a second! }
